President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster for the Navajo Nation and authorized Federal aid to assist with the aftermath of a snowstorm and flooding that occurred from February 21 to February 24, 2019. The Federal funding will be available to the Navajo Nation and certain private nonprofit organizations to help with emergency work resulting from the snowstorm and flooding. The funding will also support snow assistance for a continuous 48-hour period and hazard mitigation measures for the Navajo Nation. Benigno Bern Ruiz has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.